Class CatalogModelEvent

All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class CatalogModelEvent
extends EventObject

This event is sent to a CatalogModelListener whenever

  • a Connection has been successfully added to or removed from the CatalogModel, or
  • the refresh method of CatalogModel has been called.
These events are transmitted just after the corresponding Content object has been added to or removed from the model. Note that in the case of REMOVE, the parent Folder no longer contains the content, and content has a null parent - that is why both are present in a CatalogModelEvent.

See Also:
CatalogModelListener, Serialized Form
